item.title: Refund and Returns Policy
item.dc:creator: admin_n8bbc4up
item.content:encoded:
This is a sample page.

Overview

Our refund and returns policy lasts 30 days. If 30 days have passed since your purchase, we can’t offer you a full refund or exchange.

To be eligible for a return, your item must be unused and in the same condition that you received it. It must also be in the original packaging.

Several types of goods are exempt from being returned. Perishable goods such as food, flowers, newspapers or magazines cannot be returned. We also do not accept products that are intimate or sanitary goods, hazardous materials, or flammable liquids or gases.

Additional non-returnable items:

  • Gift cards
  • Downloadable software products
  • Some health and personal care items

To complete your return, we require a receipt or proof of purchase.

Please do not send your purchase back to the manufacturer.

There are certain situations where only partial refunds are granted:

  • Book with obvious signs of use
  • CD, DVD, VHS tape, software, video game, cassette tape, or vinyl record that has been opened.
  • Any item not in its original condition, is damaged or missing parts for reasons not due to our error.
  • Any item that is returned more than 30 days after delivery

Refunds

Once your return is received and inspected, we will send you an email to notify you that we have received your returned item. We will also notify you of the approval or rejection of your refund.

If you are approved, then your refund will be processed, and a credit will automatically be applied to your credit card or original method of payment, within a certain amount of days.

Late or missing refunds

If you haven’t received a refund yet, first check your bank account again.

Then contact your credit card company, it may take some time before your refund is officially posted.

Next contact your bank. There is often some processing time before a refund is posted.

If you’ve done all of this and you still have not received your refund yet, please contact us at {email address}.

Sale items

Only regular priced items may be refunded. Sale items cannot be refunded.

Exchanges

We only replace items if they are defective or damaged. If you need to exchange it for the same item, send us an email at {email address} and send your item to: {physical address}.

Gifts

If the item was marked as a gift when purchased and shipped directly to you, you’ll receive a gift credit for the value of your return. Once the returned item is received, a gift certificate will be mailed to you.

If the item wasn’t marked as a gift when purchased, or the gift giver had the order shipped to themselves to give to you later, we will send a refund to the gift giver and they will find out about your return.

Shipping returns

To return your product, you should mail your product to: {physical address}.

You will be responsible for paying for your own shipping costs for returning your item. Shipping costs are non-refundable. If you receive a refund, the cost of return shipping will be deducted from your refund.

Depending on where you live, the time it may take for your exchanged product to reach you may vary.

If you are returning more expensive items, you may consider using a trackable shipping service or purchasing shipping insurance. We don’t guarantee that we will receive your returned item.

Need help?

Contact us at {email} for questions related to refunds and returns.

item.dc:creator: admin_n8bbc4up
item.content:encoded:
In the labyrinthine depths of a bustling bazaar, where crimson silks fluttered like exotic birds and haggling voices rose like an intoxicating symphony, resided a peculiar emporium known as "The Emporium of Ephemeral Enchantments." Its weathered facade, adorned with peeling paint and crooked signage, seemed to whisper tales of forgotten magic and whimsical secrets. Inside, chaos reigned supreme. Potions bubbled merrily in mismatched kettles, their emerald fumes swirling with the scent of moonflowers and dragon scales. Shelves groaned under the weight of dusty tomes promising arcane knowledge and forgotten lore. Glowing crystals pulsed with unseen energies, casting an otherworldly light on stacks of ornately crafted wands and tarnished amulets.

At the heart of this eccentric haven, perched upon a throne fashioned from an enormous amethyst geode, sat Esmeralda, the enigmatic proprietor. Her emerald eyes, as wise and deep as the ocean, twinkled with mischief and held the secrets of countless lifetimes. Her raven hair, streaked with silver like moonlight on a stormy sea, was adorned with feathers of exotic birds, each whisperingly echoing forgotten languages. With a flick of her wrist, she could conjure shimmering illusions or mend a broken heart with a whispered incantation. Her laughter, like the tinkling of wind chimes, could fill the emporium with warmth or send shivers down the spine of the boldest adventurer.

One blustery afternoon, a young woman named Anya, her cloak dripping with rain, stumbled into the emporium, seeking refuge from the storm and perhaps a little more. Curiosity tugged at her like an invisible thread, drawing her deeper into the labyrinthine aisles. Amidst the curiosities, she found a tarnished locket, its inscription hinting at a love story lost to time. Anya, a dreamer with a heart yearning for adventure, felt an inexplicable pull towards it. Driven by an unseen force, she approached Esmeralda, who, with a knowing smile, revealed the locket's tale – a tale of star-crossed lovers and a hidden treasure guarded by ancient magic.

Intrigued by the enigmatic proprietor and the locket's whispered story, Anya embarked on a perilous journey, guided by cryptic clues and whispered enchantments. She braved enchanted forests where gnarled trees whispered forgotten secrets, followed shimmering starlights across treacherous mountain paths, and outsmarted mischievous sprites guarding hidden portals. As she delved deeper into the heart of the mystery, she uncovered not only the treasure but also a hidden truth about herself, a strength she never knew she possessed.

With each challenge overcome, Anya's bond with Esmeralda deepened. The enigmatic woman, initially a veiled figure, became a mentor, a confidante, and a source of unwavering support. Through her guidance, Anya learned to harness her own hidden magic, a magic woven from courage, compassion, and an unwavering belief in the impossible.

Finally, after confronting a cunning sorceress and outwitting a band of thieving gnomes, Anya reached the treasure – not a chest overflowing with gold and jewels, but a hidden library containing forgotten knowledge and lost wisdom. This was a treasure more valuable than any gold, a legacy waiting to be rediscovered. As Anya emerged from the labyrinth, transformed by her journey and armed with newfound knowledge, she knew her adventures were far from over. The world beyond the bazaar hummed with the promise of more stories waiting to be unearthed, more enchantments waiting to be discovered. And with Esmeralda by her side, a mischievous twinkle in her emerald eyes, Anya knew she was ready to face them all.

item.title: A Rose Is A Woody Perennial
item.dc:creator: admin_n8bbc4up
item.content:encoded:
In the heart of a bustling metropolis, nestled amongst towering steel and glass giants, resided a unique establishment known as "Curio & Craft." Its weathered brick facade, adorned with a discreet brass plaque, exuded an air of quiet wisdom and hidden knowledge. Inside, an air of curated chaos reigned. Glass display cases held meticulously categorized artifacts – fossilized ammonites whispering tales of ancient oceans, hand-blown vials shimmering with iridescent potions, and weathered maps hinting at unexplored territories. Shelves groaned under the weight of leather-bound tomes, their pages promising arcane insights and forgotten lore.

At the helm of this haven of hidden wonders stood Ms. Evelyn Thorne, a woman whose sharp intellect and enigmatic demeanor commanded respect. Her steely gaze, though softened by a hint of warmth, hinted at a life steeped in experience and veiled secrets. Her silver hair, streaked with the wisdom of years, was often adorned with intricate silver pins, each a testament to her travels and triumphs. Ms. Thorne possessed a unique alchemy; the ability to blend meticulous research with audacious intuition, guiding explorers and scholars alike towards their desired curiosities.

One crisp autumn morning, Dr. Anya Patel, a renowned anthropologist whose thirst for knowledge mirrored the vastness of the Sahara, stepped into Curio & Craft. Anya, driven by a grant proposal requiring an unearthed artifact with historical significance, sought Ms. Thorne's expertise. Drawn by the allure of whispered enchantments and veiled secrets, Anya found herself captivated by a worn wooden amulet, its intricate carvings hinting at forgotten rituals and potent energies.
